Auth Service Testing Guide (Detailed)

You’ve built these APIs:

POST /auth/register
POST /auth/login
POST /auth/refresh
POST /auth/send-otp
POST /auth/verify-otp

Now let’s test them properly end-to-end.

1. Pre-Requisites Before Testing
Services Running

Start in this order:

1. Eureka Server (8761)
2. API Gateway (8080)
3. Auth Service (8081)
2. Verify Eureka Dashboard

Open:

http://localhost:8761

You should see:

AUTH-SERVICE
API-GATEWAY

Status = UP

3. Verify Gateway Route

Since gateway routes:

/auth/**

You should call:

http://localhost:8080/auth/...

Not directly 8081 (unless testing service alone).

4. Use Postman / Insomnia / curl

Recommended: Postman

Create collection:

Auth Service APIs
5. Test Case 1 — Register User
Endpoint
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "email": "user1@gmail.com",
  "username": "bharadwaj",
  "password": "Secret@123"
}
Expected Response
Registered Successfully
DB Validation

Check users_auth table:

select * from users_auth;

Expected:

email saved
username saved
password_hash encrypted
uuid generated
role USER
status ACTIVE
6. Test Case 2 — Duplicate Register

Try same request again.

Expected
Email already exists

(If no global exception handler, maybe 500 for now.)

7. Test Case 3 — Login Success
Endpoint
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "email": "user1@gmail.com",
  "password": "Secret@123"
}
Expected Response
{
  "accessToken": "access-user1@gmail.com-....",
  "refreshToken": "refresh-user1@gmail.com-...."
}
DB Validation

Check refresh token stored:

select * from refresh_tokens;
8. Test Case 4 — Login Wrong Password
Body
{
  "email": "user1@gmail.com",
  "password": "wrongpass"
}
Expected
Invalid Password
9. Test Case 5 — Refresh Token

Use refresh token from login response.

Endpoint
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "refreshToken": "refresh-user1@gmail.com-...."
}
Expected
{
  "accessToken": "new-access-token",
  "refreshToken": "same-refresh-token"
}
